<div class="container">
    <div class="legal-header">
        <span class="legal-subtitle">Transparency & Trust</span>
        <h1 class="legal-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="legal-meta">Last Updated: October 10th, 2024</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-grid">

        <aside class="legal-sidebar">
            <nav class="legal-nav">
                <a href="#intro" class="active">01. Introduction</a>
                <a href="#collection">02. Information We Collect</a>
                <a href="#sharing">03. Sharing & Disclosure</a>
                <a href="#cookies">04. Cookies & Tracking</a>
                <a href="#rights">05. Your Rights</a>
                <a href="#contact">06. Contact Us</a>
            </nav>
        </aside>

        <article class="legal-content">

            <section id="intro">
                <p class="intro-text">
                    At Le Vount, we believe that privacy is the ultimate luxury. We are committed to
                    protecting your personal information with the same care and precision we apply to our jewelry.
                    This policy outlines how we handle your data.
                    <br>
                    By accessing or using our website, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy.
                    If you do not agree with the practices described in this policy, please do not use our services.
                </p>
            </section>

            <section id="collection">
                <h2>01. Information We Collect</h2>
                <p>
                    To provide you with a seamless shopping experience and curated service, we collect the following
                    types of information:
                </p>
                <h3>Information You Provide Directly</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Identity Data:</strong> First name, last name, and ring size preferences.</li>
                    <li><strong>Contact Data:</strong> Shipping address, billing address, and email address (for "The Le
                        Vount List" or order updates).</li>
                    <li><strong>Transaction Data:</strong> Details about payments and products you have purchased from
                        us. Note that <strong>we do not store your credit card information</strong> on our servers;
                        transactions are processed securely by third-party providers (e.g., Stripe, PayPal).</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Information Collected Automatically</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Technical Data:</strong> IP address, browser type, time zone setting, and device
                        information.</li>
                    <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Information about how you use our website, products, and services.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Security Data:</strong> We use Cloudflare Turnstile to distinguish between human users
                        and bots to protect our site infrastructure.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="usage">
                <h2>02. How We Use Your Information</h2>
                <p>We use your personal data only when the law allows us to. Most commonly, we use your personal data in
                    the following circumstances:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Order Fulfillment:</strong> To process and deliver your jewelry, manage payments, and
                        handle returns.</li>
                    <li><strong>Concierge Service:</strong> To respond to your inquiries regarding sizing, care
                        instructions, or order status.</li>
                    <li><strong>Communication:</strong> To send you transactional emails (order confirmations) and, if
                        you have opted in, our newsletter regarding new collections and exclusive access.</li>
                    <li><strong>Security & Fraud Prevention:</strong> To protect our website and your account from
                        unauthorized access or fraudulent transactions.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="sharing">
                <h2>03. Sharing & Disclosure</h2>
                <p><strong>We do not sell your personal data.</strong> Transparency is key to our relationship with you.
                    We only share your data with trusted third parties who assist us in operating our website and
                    conducting our business:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> Payment processors, shipping partners (e.g., FedEx, DHL),
                        and email service providers.</li>
                    <li><strong>Legal Obligations:</strong> We may disclose your information if required to do so by law
                        or in response to valid requests by public authorities.</li>
                    <li><strong>Business Transfers:</strong> In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a
                        portion of our assets, your data may be transferred as part of that transaction.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="cookies">
                <h2>04. Cookies & Tracking Technologies</h2>
                <p>Our website uses cookies to enhance your browsing experience. Specifically, we use:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Essential Cookies:</strong> These are necessary for the website to function (e.g.,
                        keeping items in your shopping bag while you navigate).</li>
                    <li><strong>Functional Cookies:</strong> These enable us to remember your preferences (such as
                        currency or region).</li>
                    <li><strong>Analytics Cookies:</strong> These help us understand how visitors interact with our
                        website, allowing us to improve our design and offerings.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>You can choose to disable cookies through your browser settings, though this may affect the
                    functionality of the shopping cart.</p>
            </section>

            <section id="rights">
                <h2>05. Your Rights</h2>
                <p>Depending on your location (including California residents under the CCPA and users in the EEA), you
                    may have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Right to Access:</strong> You can request a copy of the personal data we hold about you.
                    </li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Correction:</strong> You can request that we correct any incomplete or
                        inaccurate data.</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Erasure:</strong> You can ask us to delete your personal data (the "Right to be
                        Forgotten"), subject to certain legal exceptions (e.g., keeping transaction records for tax
                        purposes).</li>
                    <li><strong>Right to Opt-Out:</strong> You can unsubscribe from "The Le Vount List" at any time by
                        clicking the "Unsubscribe" link in the footer of our emails.</li>
                </ul>
            </section>

            <section id="contact">
                <h2>06. Contact Us</h2>
                <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise your rights, please contact
                    our team:</p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@levount.com">support@levount.com</a><br>
                </p>
            </section>

